  "market_context": "DXY is trending lower after a bearish engulfing monthly candle, respecting the lower half of that candle and continuing in a downward trajectory on the daily timeframe.",
  "key_observation": "With DXY bearish, the analyst surveys the foreign currency futures to identify which are strongest (bullish) and weakest, finding EUR and JPY as the strongest candidates while GBP, CAD, NZD and AUD are bearish or weak.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Establish dollar bias as bearish based on the bearish engulfing monthly candle and continuation lower on DXY daily chart.",
    "Step 2: Review foreign currency futures to find bullish counterparts — Euro is bullish, Pound is not as strong, Yen is quite bullish, CAD is bearish, Swissy is strong but has hit a target, NZD and AUD are bearish.",
    "Step 3: Narrow focus to JPY and Euro as the strongest bullish foreign currencies to pair against the weak dollar.",
    "Step 4: Select EUR/USD (long bias) and USD/JPY (short bias) as the pairs to trade for the next day.",
    "Step 5: Play forward and confirm USD/JPY expanded lower while EUR/USD expanded higher, validating the pairing selection.",
    "Step 6: Contrast with GBP/USD, which did not produce an expansion day, demonstrating why proper currency selection via futures matters."
  ],
  "outcome": "Both pairings worked: USD/JPY delivered an expansion lower and EUR/USD delivered an expansion higher the following day.",
  "lessons": "Always begin with a dollar bias, then pair it with foreign currencies showing the opposite directional strength. Reviewing currency futures helps identify the strongest and weakest pairs, ensuring alignment for expansion and avoiding weak setups like GBP/USD.",
